-"Forgive me."

303
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:03,653
"I can't stand it any longer."

304
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,239
We may get to hear those lines
in Kansai dialect.

305
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:07,865
What situations are you imagining?

306
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:10,827
The Japanese-style room, of course.

307
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:15,748
She'll like someone so much and say,
"I can't stand it any longer."

308
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:19,710
-We might get to hear it.
-You're right.

309
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:22,672
"I've overcooked the sprouts!"

310
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,966
-We might get to hear that.
-We just might.

311
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:28,136
She might say it,
but the staff might edit that one out.

312
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:32,807
And Hikaru is sort of...

313
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:37,353
-He seems into Arisa.
-It seems like he'll make a move on her.

314
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:42,066
This month, I'll be a shut-in.
Or what's the word?

315
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:44,360
You're stuck inside?

316
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:47,530
I have so much work.

317
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:48,739
It's crazy.

318
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,742
But isn't it better to stay busy?

319
00:15:51,826 --> 00:15:53,035
-Yeah, it's fun.
-Right?

320
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:57,331
You have unnecessary thoughts
when you have too much free time.

321
00:15:57,415 --> 00:15:59,500
I love having free time.

322
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:05,756
I can live forever doing nothing.

323
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,926
Having time off as a student

324
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:12,680
and having time off while working
are pretty different, aren't they?

325
00:16:12,763 --> 00:16:15,349
Age definitely makes a difference.

326
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:18,436
Every year, I realize
how long I've been in Tokyo,

327
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,730
and I panic.

328
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:25,109
Makes me think, "What am I doing?"

329
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,281
Oh, so, what do you like about him?

330
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:34,118
-Oh, we're continuing that?
-I just remembered.

331
00:16:34,202 --> 00:16:36,078
-Uchi?
-Yeah.

332
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:38,831
She wouldn't clearly say.

333
00:16:38,915 --> 00:16:41,584
They kept putting each other down.

334
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,003
I've never seen a couple like that.

335
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:47,423
He's your boyfriend,
but I felt some distance between you.

336
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:50,218
They're different from a normal couple,

337
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:53,638
but I just figured
that's just Minori and Uchi.

338
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:56,599
Is it different when you two are alone?

339
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:59,143
-It's the same.
-Really?

340
00:16:59,227 --> 00:17:02,188
For example, I'm really obvious.

341
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,148
I'm always touching my boyfriends.

342
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:06,609
-Really?
-Yeah.

343
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:11,989
To an outside observer,
we'd look like a lovey-dovey couple.

344
00:17:12,073 --> 00:17:16,536
It's easy to imagine
a couple like that kissing.

345
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:20,706
But couples
that are always making fun of each other,

346
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:22,959
I don't really understand.

347
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:26,921
It's harder to imagine them kissing.

348
00:17:27,547 --> 00:17:30,800
-Do you have to be able to imagine it?
-No, but...

349
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:35,054
They just don't give
that impression in public, I think.

350
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:41,978
-That's...
-You laugh, but it's true!

351
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,689
You guys are probably
just complete opposites.

352
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:47,108
Total opposites.

353
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:53,406
-I'm so tired today.
-It's tough to get used to.

354
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,408
It's hard.

355
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:56,909
Feel like you'll fit in?

356
00:17:56,993 --> 00:17:59,996
No one seems like a bad person.

357
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:03,541
If you were to pick now,
which girl would be your type?

358
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,085
-By their face? Their looks?
-By looks.

359
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,545
By looks?

360
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:10,047
I think Arisa is cute.

361
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:15,136
-I see. Arisa.
-If we're going by looks, she's my type.

362
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:17,555
We'll see what happens.

363
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:20,933
What did you guys talk about
in the game room?

364
00:18:21,017 --> 00:18:26,022
We both like the ocean,
so... she suggested we go to the beach.

365
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,649
She asked?

366
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:31,986
That's exactly what happened with Arisa!

367
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:33,904
I can't believe it.

368
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:36,073
-She works fast.
-So you're going to the beach?

369
00:18:36,157 --> 00:18:37,742
I guess so.

370
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:41,704
What happens to you?

371
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:45,875
I lose my words with people I like.

372
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:49,795
-You make them like you?
-How do you mean?

373
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,425
-I wish I could make them like me.
-You seem like you do it unconsciously.

374
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:56,093
Me?

375
00:18:56,177 --> 00:18:58,346
Do I?

376
00:18:58,429 --> 00:19:00,473
Is there someone
you'd like to be with right now?

377
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,266
No.

378
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:06,103
But...

379
00:19:08,189 --> 00:19:10,816
there is someone I have fun with.

380
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:14,403
Well, it could only be one person.

381
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:17,156
Yeah, I have fun with him.

382
00:19:18,199 --> 00:19:19,450
-Do you think you'll fall for him?
-Hmm?

383
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,701
Do you think you'll fall for him?

384
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:23,245
Wow!

385
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:26,624
So many questions!

386
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:31,212
I'm going to be living here.
Of course I'd want to know!

387
00:19:31,295 --> 00:19:34,882
What about you?

388
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:37,551
I felt like everyone was reserved.

389
00:19:37,635 --> 00:19:40,721
-Today was more energetic than usual.
-No way!

390
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:43,140
I was more energetic than usual.

391
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:44,892
It was fun today.

392
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:48,104
I'm glad you're here.
You bring fun energy.

393
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:08,124
Wow. You set up the room?

394
00:20:08,791 --> 00:20:10,418
It's cold.

395
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:14,839
-You want to sleep here?
-You don't want to sleep downstairs?

396
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:20,970
I wasn't sure since there's a new guy.

397
00:20:22,263 --> 00:20:24,682
-Did you girls talk?
-Yeah, we talked.

398
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:28,602
-She's scary.
-Scary? How come?

399
00:20:28,686 --> 00:20:30,688
She immediately asked.

400
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:34,275
-About what?
-How things are with us.

401
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:37,528
You know how she asked
what I liked about you earlier?

402
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,280
She asked me again.

403
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,949
She said all we did was
to make fun of each other.

404
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:43,909
She said it's weird.

405
00:20:43,993 --> 00:20:49,457
She asked about when we're alone,
and I told her we're the same.

406
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:52,168
Then she asked if we're okay.

407
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,878
We're okay.

408
00:20:53,961 --> 00:21:00,050
She made it sound like
there was something wrong with us.

409
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:02,470
That seems rude.

410
00:21:02,553 --> 00:21:07,224
She wouldn't let it go.
I was a little ticked.

411
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:16,025
-There might be a conflict.
-She totally says what's on her mind.

412
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:17,610
Yeah, she seems like she does.

413
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:20,780
Like she can't accept people
that are different from her.

414
00:21:20,863 --> 00:21:23,532
-I got a little of that from her.
-Then she's like me.

415
00:21:23,616 --> 00:21:25,242
-Will you be okay?
-I don't know.

416
00:21:25,326 --> 00:21:27,077
Will you be able to get along?

