490
00:26:35,594 --> 00:26:40,349
And after this encounter,
Natsumi left for China for work.

491
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:43,060
Hopefully, there won't be
some strange meetings.

492
00:26:43,143 --> 00:26:46,814
Yeah, a trial in absentia.
The trial in absentia from hell.

493
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:48,857
"Those Kansai people..."

494
00:26:50,317 --> 00:26:52,444
"Oh, look, the takoyaki came back."

495
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,322
Oh, they could make jokes!

496
00:26:55,405 --> 00:26:58,534
"The wheels on your luggage,
are they actually takoyaki?"

497
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:01,703
It would be refreshing
if they could say that.

498
00:27:01,787 --> 00:27:04,248
We're worried because they can't.

499
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:06,250
You Kansai people can do that.

500
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:18,846
No one's home?

501
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:24,476
Didn't Nacchan say she's going to China?

502
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:25,686
Yeah, she left.

503
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:27,563
-She left today?
-Yeah, this morning.

504
00:27:29,231 --> 00:27:31,567
-What time?
-I don't know. Pretty early.

505
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,986
-Before I left?
-Way before.

506
00:27:34,069 --> 00:27:35,487
I didn't notice.

507
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:39,324
-I'm back.
-Welcome back.

508
00:27:39,408 --> 00:27:41,743
-I'm back.
-Welcome back.

509
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:44,288
Was she at work?

510
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,707
-I guess she was at work.
-Yeah.

511
00:27:51,587 --> 00:27:54,006
-You're not joining us?
-What?

512
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:55,591
-You're not joining us?
-Later.

513
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:56,842
Okay.

514
00:28:01,305 --> 00:28:02,389
She seems tired.

515
00:28:02,472 --> 00:28:05,350
-We should talk more though.
-Yeah.

516
00:28:10,772 --> 00:28:12,024
Are you drinking?

517
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,275
-No.
-Yes.

518
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:14,484
-You're drinking?
-Yeah.

519
00:28:14,568 --> 00:28:17,154
-You are?
-Yeah.

520
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:19,990
-Do you want a drink?
-No, not today.

521
00:28:20,073 --> 00:28:22,075
-Work?
-There's that,

522
00:28:22,159 --> 00:28:24,828
but I also wanted to make udon for dinner.

523
00:28:24,912 --> 00:28:27,831
-Right now?
-I haven't eaten yet.

524
00:28:27,915 --> 00:28:30,792
And Minori said she hasn't eaten either.

525
00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:33,921
Did you know Minori caught a cold?

526
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:37,007
Yeah, she looked like she was dying.

527
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:38,508
Does it look bad?

528
00:28:38,592 --> 00:28:42,304
Her fever's gone down,
but she said her stomach hurts.

529
00:28:42,387 --> 00:28:43,889
Her stomach?
Is she okay?

530
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:47,935
I think it's
because she hasn't eaten any carbs.

531
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:50,479
-She went to the hospital?
-Yesterday.

532
00:28:52,481 --> 00:28:55,275
How are things?
We didn't talk over the break.

533
00:28:55,359 --> 00:29:00,989
-Recently?
-Do you have your hands full with work?

534
00:29:02,074 --> 00:29:04,910
Since the new year began,
all I've done is work.

535
00:29:06,245 --> 00:29:09,373
I don't think I'll have time off.

536
00:29:10,624 --> 00:29:12,793
You work every day? No breaks?

537
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:16,880
Vendors are off, so I could rest, but...

538
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:20,384
You don't have set breaks?
Like on weekends?

539
00:29:20,467 --> 00:29:24,137
I could if I wanted to.

540
00:29:24,221 --> 00:29:27,432
But I have way too much to do.

541
00:29:27,516 --> 00:29:31,728
I have things I need to finish this week.

542
00:29:33,146 --> 00:29:35,232
Do you guys want some udon?

543
00:29:35,315 --> 00:29:37,818
I don't.
You must be hungry.

544
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:41,738
-Is there enough?
-I have three packs.

545
00:29:41,822 --> 00:29:43,282
-Really?
-Yeah.

546
00:29:43,365 --> 00:29:45,158
-I'll have some.
-Okay.

547
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:52,291
-She is cute.
-She is.

548
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:55,460
I wonder if she heard.

549
00:29:56,253 --> 00:30:00,132
She's cute, but she seems busy.

550
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:13,228
If you're still interested in her
after a week,

551
00:30:13,312 --> 00:30:17,524
don't worry about me.
Just go for it.

552
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:19,026
For Arisa?

553
00:30:19,109 --> 00:30:21,570
It doesn't have to be now.

554
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,447
But something might still happen
between you two, right?

555
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:27,451
-Yeah, it seems so.
-Then you should keep approaching.

556
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:31,997
If we get to know each other...

557
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,541
and if I end up liking her,

558
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:37,294
I'm usually not bothered by other guys.

559
00:30:37,377 --> 00:30:38,879
I usually think about myself first.

560
00:30:38,962 --> 00:30:40,589
That's for the best.

561
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:42,799
I'll make my move then.

